{"_id":"antoniosalchemyvials001","name":"Antonio's Alchemical Vials","type":"object","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_circle.webp","system":{"description":"Series of alchemical compounds in vials that Antonio Ciliegia hides in his tunic. However, due to his proverbial bad luck, on rolls of 5-6 something goes wrong and Antonio suffers 1 Wound. Effects: 1. Fire (target and area catch fire, 1 Wound, continues burning until extinguished), 2. Thunder (target knocked thirty feet away, 1 Wound if hits obstacle), 3. Glue (adhesive compound paralyzes target until removed, glue can take 2 Wounds). Despite his skills and experience, Antonio's legendary misfortune makes his own alchemy dangerous to himself.","quantity":6,"weight":1,"value":200,"equipped":false,"properties":["Alchemical compounds","Hidden in tunic","Fire bombs","Thunder knockback","Paralyzing glue","Unlucky backfires on 5-6"],"scenario":"of-flesh-and-wood"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"carlosoldsho es001","name":"Carlo's Elegant Old Shoes","type":"clue","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_circle.webp","system":{"description":"Pair of old, elegant shoes that Geppetto gave to Carlo for his first day of school. Despite Carlo using his lies power to disguise himself as a real child and not matching Geppetto's description, these distinctive shoes on his feet are the only clue that allows the Hunters to identify the living puppet among the schoolchildren. The shoes are recognizable and connect Carlo to Geppetto's fabricated story of the lost son.","location":"On Carlo's feet at the School or Villa Balocchi","importance":"important","found":false,"scenario":"of-flesh-and-wood"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"carlosfalsegold001","name":"Carlo's False Gold Coins","type":"clue","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_circle.webp","system":{"description":"Stones that Carlo temporarily turns into gold coins using his lies power to pay Amabile Burromo, the greedy innkeeper at Villa Balocchi. The puppet creates these false coins to pay for his lodging in a small back room. Throwing the coins into a safe in his room, the innkeeper hasn't yet noticed the trick - the gold will eventually revert to ordinary stones once Carlo's lie magic fades. Evidence of Carlo's deceptive nature and his ability to manipulate reality through lies.","location":"Villa Balocchi - Amabile's safe in his room","importance":"important","found":false,"scenario":"of-flesh-and-wood"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"geppettosalchemyvials001","name":"Geppetto's Alchemical Vials","type":"object","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_circle.webp","system":{"description":"Series of alchemical compounds contained in vials that Geppetto hides under his tacky yellow wig. When thrown, vials produce random effects: 1-2 Explosive (1 Wound to everyone within thirty feet, thick black smoke engulfs area), 3-4 Stench (nauseating odor giving 1 Penalty to all actions for rest of Scene), 5-6 Air Bomb (all subjects within thirty feet knocked back and fall to ground, 1 Wound if hit obstacle). Geppetto is immune to his own concoctions' effects.","quantity":6,"weight":1,"value":200,"equipped":false,"properties":["Alchemical compounds","Hidden under yellow wig","Random explosive effects","Stench clouds","Knockback bombs","User immune to effects"],"scenario":"of-flesh-and-wood"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"geppettoschisel001","name":"Geppetto's Carpenter Chisel","type":"clue","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_circle.webp","system":{"description":"A carpenter's chisel that Geppetto lost while moving the corpses at the bottom of the old well. This tool belongs to the set of chisels displayed on the wall of Mastro Antonio's old carpenter shop. When the Hunters find it at the bottom of the well among remaining corpses and blood traces, they can match it to the missing tool from the set in the workshop, directly linking the alchemists to the murders.","location":"The Old Well - bottom, among blood traces and remains","importance":"crucial","found":false,"scenario":"of-flesh-and-wood"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"ninoapprentice001","name":"Nino the Flayed Apprentice","type":"clue","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_circle.webp","system":{"description":"Mastro Antonio's apprentice carpenter, the 11th missing person whose body was never found with the others in the well. Nino is tied to a table in the Secret Laboratory, alive but with his legs now ruined by Antonio's slow, methodical flaying. Azzurra wants him kept alive because she needs innocent blood for her resurrection rite. Nino represents the most immediate and horrific evidence of the alchemists' crimes, and rescuing him may be crucial to stopping Azzurra's ritual.","location":"Villa Cilesterino - Secret Laboratory, tied to table","importance":"crucial","found":false,"scenario":"of-flesh-and-wood"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"schoolbooksbag001","name":"School Books in Leather Bag","type":"clue","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_circle.webp","system":{"description":"Old leather bag containing books for the local school, found among other things of interest in the Old Carpenter's Shop. These books belong to Carlo and show his attempt to live as a normal child attending school in Sinalunga. The presence of school supplies in the abandoned workshop connects Carlo to the carpenter's shop and suggests his recent presence there before he escaped.","location":"Old Carpenter's Shop - among items of interest","importance":"minor","found":false,"scenario":"of-flesh-and-wood"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"ancientalchemytext001","name":"The Ancient Alchemical Text","type":"clue","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_circle.webp","system":{"description":"Ancient text in possession of Antonio and Geppetto that revealed the alchemical formula for eternal life. According to the text, the key component is a body made of enchanted wood - mystical material that would bestow immortality. However, to live among humans without frightening them, the wooden body must be covered in flesh. This text led the two alchemists to their gruesome experiments combining wood and human skin.","location":"Villa Cilesterino - Secret Laboratory or Old Carpenter's Shop","importance":"crucial","found":false,"scenario":"of-flesh-and-wood"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"bloodstainedmannequins001","name":"The Bloodstained Mannequins","type":"clue","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_circle.webp","system":{"description":"Two human-sized wooden mannequins hanging on the wall at the back of the Old Carpenter's Shop. Skillfully made but horrifyingly stained with blood and decomposing human skin. These are the first two Marionettes produced by Antonio and Geppetto's experiments, later animated by Azzurra's magic to contain cursed souls. The mannequins show clear evidence of the alchemists' gruesome work combining wood with flayed human flesh. They will spring on the Hunters as soon as they approach.","location":"Old Carpenter's Shop - back wall, near alchemical laboratory remains","importance":"crucial","found":false,"scenario":"of-flesh-and-wood"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"magicalbrazier001","name":"The Magical Brazier","type":"clue","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_circle.webp","system":{"description":"Magical brazier created by Antonio in the Secret Laboratory under Azzurra's guidance. This alchemical device is specifically designed to burn Carlo, the living puppet, as part of Azzurra's dark ritual to use the fairy magic animating him to bring herself back to life. The brazier represents the culmination of Antonio's research and Azzurra's manipulation of the alchemists. It is the key instrument for the witch's resurrection ritual.","location":"Villa Cilesterino - Secret Laboratory cellar","importance":"crucial","found":false,"scenario":"of-flesh-and-wood"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"magicaloakwood001","name":"The Magical Oak Wood","type":"clue","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_circle.webp","system":{"description":"Mystical oak tree that Antonio and Geppetto worked on, hoping to obtain the fantastic ingredients for eternal life. During experiments, the two alchemists discovered the magical oak had a life of its own. Animated by fairy magic whose only purpose is to bedevil humans, this enchanted piece of wood could bring lies to life. The oak transformed itself into Carlo, the living wooden puppet.","location":"Originally at Old Carpenter's Shop, manifested as Carlo","importance":"crucial","found":false,"scenario":"of-flesh-and-wood"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"whalepainting001","name":"The Whale Painting with Secret Door","type":"clue","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_circle.webp","system":{"description":"Huge painting in Villa Cilesterino's dining room depicting a whale swallowing entire ships. Behind the painting is hidden a mechanism that opens a secret door leading to the Secret Laboratory in the cellar. By looking behind the painting, the Hunters can activate the mechanism and access Antonio's underground alchemical laboratory where the most horrific experiments take place. The whale imagery is a direct reference to Pinocchio's tale.","location":"Villa Cilesterino - Dining room, north wall","importance":"crucial","found":false,"scenario":"of-flesh-and-wood"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
